Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pour enough @oil{cover bottom} into a deep #baking tray{} to cover the bottom and pop in the oven.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil. Peel and chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 3cm chunks.

Boil the potatoes for ~{7-8%minutes} or until the edges are soft.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g}. Pick the @tarragon{1/2}(leaves picked and finely chopped) leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, lay the @Serrano hams{2} in the pan and fry until crisp, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Once crispy, transfer to a plate covered in kitchen paper. Set aside.

Return your (now empty) #pan{} to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{} if it's a little dry. Season the @British chicken breasts{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When hot, lay in the chicken breasts and cook until golden brown all over, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

When the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{}. Shake to fluff up the potatoes, then carefully add them to the hot baking tray, turning in the oil.

Season with @salt{}, then roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Once the chicken is browned all over, add the mushrooms to the pan and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: If your pan is small, remove the chicken from the pan, then cook the mushrooms and return the chicken once they're cooked.

Pour in the @water for the sauce{300%ml} and @wild mushroom paste{2%tbsp}. Stir well to combine, bring to the boil, then lower the heat.

Cover with a #lid{} or #foil{} and simmer until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Fill the (now empty) potato pan with water and put on to boil. Halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

When your pan of water is boiling, add @salt{1/4%tsp} and the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g}. Cook until just tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

When the mushroom sauce has thickened, stir the @creme fraiche{150%g} through, bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

When everything is ready, plate up each chicken breast with the broccoli and roast potatoes alongside.

Stir the tarragon and half the @truffle zest{1%tsp}(split into halves) into the mushroom sauce, then spoon over the chicken.

Finish by topping with a Serrano ham crisp and a sprinkle of the remaining truffle zest.

Enjoy!